<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <%- include('../layouts/head', { title: title, seo: typeof seo !== 'undefined' ? seo : null }) %>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/how-it-works.css">
</head>
<body class="how-body">
  <%- include('../layouts/nav') %>

  <main class="how-page">
    <header class="how-hero">
      <div class="how-wrap how-hero-inner">
        <div class="how-hero-copy">
          <span class="how-kicker"><i data-lucide="route" aria-hidden="true"></i> One event. Two connected journeys.</span>
          <h1>How HelloRun events work</h1>
          <p>See what runners and organizers do at every stage—from clear event rules and registration to reviewed results and recognition.</p>
        </div>
        <nav class="how-perspectives" aria-label="Choose your perspective">
          <a class="how-perspective how-perspective-runner" href="#runner-path">
            <i data-lucide="person-standing" aria-hidden="true"></i>
            <span><small>Runner path</small>I’m joining an event</span>
            <i data-lucide="arrow-down" aria-hidden="true"></i>
          </a>
          <a class="how-perspective how-perspective-organizer" href="#organizer-path">
            <i data-lucide="clipboard-check" aria-hidden="true"></i>
            <span><small>Organizer path</small>I’m organizing an event</span>
            <i data-lucide="arrow-down" aria-hidden="true"></i>
          </a>
        </nav>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section class="how-format-band" aria-labelledby="event-formats-title">
      <div class="how-wrap how-formats">
        <h2 id="event-formats-title">Built for the way your event works</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><i data-lucide="smartphone" aria-hidden="true"></i>Virtual</li>
          <li><i data-lucide="map-pin" aria-hidden="true"></i>On-site</li>
          <li><i data-lucide="shuffle" aria-hidden="true"></i>Hybrid</li>
          <li><i data-lucide="timer" aria-hidden="true"></i>Single result</li>
          <li><i data-lucide="bar-chart-3" aria-hidden="true"></i>Accumulated distance</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="how-wrap how-content">
      <section class="how-section how-lifecycle-section" aria-labelledby="lifecycle-title">
        <div class="how-section-heading">
          <span class="how-heading-icon"><i data-lucide="git-merge" aria-hidden="true"></i></span>
          <div>
            <span class="how-eyebrow">The shared lifecycle</span>
            <h2 id="lifecycle-title">What happens—and what comes next</h2>
            <p>Each lane stays connected, so runners know what is expected and organizers know what they must confirm.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="how-lifecycle" role="list">
          <div class="how-lifecycle-labels" aria-hidden="true">
            <span>Stage</span><span>Runner</span><span>Organizer</span>
          </div>

          <article class="how-stage-row" role="listitem">
            <div class="how-stage-marker"><span>01</span><strong>Publish</strong></div>
            <div class="how-lane how-runner-lane" id="runner-path" tabindex="-1">
              <span class="how-lane-label"><i data-lucide="person-standing" aria-hidden="true"></i>Runner</span>
              <h3>Read the event rules</h3>
              <p>Check the organizer, dates, category, pricing, accepted activity, proof, and deadline before committing.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="how-lane how-organizer-lane" id="organizer-path" tabindex="-1">
              <span class="how-lane-label"><i data-lucide="clipboard-check" aria-hidden="true"></i>Organizer</span>
              <h3>Publish complete, accurate rules</h3>
              <p>Set the event window, categories, fees, proof requirements, review process, and recognition before opening registration.</p>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="how-stage-row" role="listitem">
            <div class="how-stage-marker"><span>02</span><strong>Register</strong></div>
            <div class="how-lane how-runner-lane">
              <span class="how-lane-label"><i data-lucide="person-standing" aria-hidden="true"></i>Runner</span>
              <h3>Choose and register</h3>
              <p>Use your correct account name, select the intended category or mode, and submit payment proof only when required.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="how-lane how-organizer-lane">
              <span class="how-lane-label"><i data-lucide="clipboard-check" aria-hidden="true"></i>Organizer</span>
              <h3>Confirm the registration</h3>
              <p>Manage capacity and registration details. Review payment separately from the runner’s later activity evidence.</p>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="how-stage-row" role="listitem">
            <div class="how-stage-marker"><span>03</span><strong>Complete</strong></div>
            <div class="how-lane how-runner-lane">
              <span class="how-lane-label"><i data-lucide="person-standing" aria-hidden="true"></i>Runner</span>
              <h3>Complete and submit</h3>
              <p>Do the accepted activity during the official window, then submit readable proof with the required details.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="how-lane how-organizer-lane">
              <span class="how-lane-label"><i data-lucide="clipboard-check" aria-hidden="true"></i>Organizer</span>
              <h3>Keep requirements clear</h3>
              <p>Make the submission window, supported activity sources, minimum evidence, and correction process easy to find.</p>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="how-stage-row" role="listitem">
            <div class="how-stage-marker"><span>04</span><strong>Review</strong></div>
            <div class="how-lane how-runner-lane">
              <span class="how-lane-label"><i data-lucide="person-standing" aria-hidden="true"></i>Runner</span>
              <h3>Follow the review status</h3>
              <p>Pending means wait. Approved means it counts. If rejected, read the reason and resubmit when the event allows it.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="how-lane how-organizer-lane">
              <span class="how-lane-label"><i data-lucide="clipboard-check" aria-hidden="true"></i>Organizer</span>
              <h3>Review evidence consistently</h3>
              <p>Check activity proof against published rules, protect private files, and give a useful reason when correction is needed.</p>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="how-stage-row" role="listitem">
            <div class="how-stage-marker"><span>05</span><strong>Recognize</strong></div>
            <div class="how-lane how-runner-lane">
              <span class="how-lane-label"><i data-lucide="person-standing" aria-hidden="true"></i>Runner</span>
              <h3>See the official outcome</h3>
              <p>Approved results may enter standings or unlock a certificate or badge when the event has enabled them.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="how-lane how-organizer-lane">
              <span class="how-lane-label"><i data-lucide="clipboard-check" aria-hidden="true"></i>Organizer</span>
              <h3>Publish trusted recognition</h3>
              <p>Keep official results based on approved evidence and expose only the public fields configured for the event.</p>
            </div>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="how-section how-submit-section" aria-labelledby="submit-title">
        <div class="how-section-heading how-section-heading-compact">
          <span class="how-heading-icon"><i data-lucide="list-checks" aria-hidden="true"></i></span>
          <div>
            <span class="how-eyebrow">Fewer delays</span>
            <h2 id="submit-title">Before you submit</h2>
          </div>
        </div>
        <ul class="how-checklist">
          <li><i data-lucide="check" aria-hidden="true"></i>Correct account name</li>
          <li><i data-lucide="check" aria-hidden="true"></i>Inside the event window</li>
          <li><i data-lucide="check" aria-hidden="true"></i>Right distance or category</li>
          <li><i data-lucide="check" aria-hidden="true"></i>Activity date is visible</li>
          <li><i data-lucide="check" aria-hidden="true"></i>Duration is visible</li>
          <li><i data-lucide="check" aria-hidden="true"></i>Activity source is visible</li>
          <li><i data-lucide="check" aria-hidden="true"></i>Proof is readable</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="how-review-note">
          <i data-lucide="split" aria-hidden="true"></i>
          <p><strong>Two separate checks:</strong> payment approval confirms a registration payment; activity-proof approval confirms the result. One does not automatically approve the other.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="how-section" aria-labelledby="event-behavior-title">
        <div class="how-section-heading">
          <span class="how-heading-icon"><i data-lucide="waypoints" aria-hidden="true"></i></span>
          <div>
            <span class="how-eyebrow">Know your goal</span>
            <h2 id="event-behavior-title">Single result or accumulated distance</h2>
            <p>The event page is always authoritative for the target, accepted activities, dates, and proof.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="how-comparison">
          <article>
            <span class="how-card-icon"><i data-lucide="flag" aria-hidden="true"></i></span>
            <div>
              <h3>Single-result events</h3>
              <p>Submit one activity for the selected distance or category. The approved record may use time, pace, or completion according to the ranking rule.</p>
            </div>
          </article>
          <article>
            <span class="how-card-icon"><i data-lucide="bar-chart-3" aria-hidden="true"></i></span>
            <div>
              <h3>Accumulated Distance Challenges</h3>
              <p>Build progress from multiple approved activities during the challenge window. Pending activities do not count toward the official total yet.</p>
            </div>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="how-section" aria-labelledby="review-title">
        <div class="how-section-heading how-section-heading-compact">
          <span class="how-heading-icon"><i data-lucide="scan-search" aria-hidden="true"></i></span>
          <div>
            <span class="how-eyebrow">After submission</span>
            <h2 id="review-title">Understand your review status</h2>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="how-status-grid">
          <article class="how-status-pending"><span><i data-lucide="clock-3" aria-hidden="true"></i>Pending</span><p>Your proof is waiting for review. No action is needed unless the organizer asks for more information.</p></article>
          <article class="how-status-approved"><span><i data-lucide="badge-check" aria-hidden="true"></i>Approved</span><p>Your verified result counts toward the event’s configured progress, standings, or recognition.</p></article>
          <article class="how-status-rejected"><span><i data-lucide="circle-x" aria-hidden="true"></i>Rejected</span><p>Read the review reason. A wrong date, missing detail, or unreadable image can prevent approval.</p></article>
          <article class="how-status-resubmit"><span><i data-lucide="refresh-cw" aria-hidden="true"></i>Resubmission</span><p>Correct the issue and submit clearer evidence before the deadline when the event permits another attempt.</p></article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="how-guidance" aria-label="Proof, recognition, and support guidance">
        <article>
          <span class="how-card-icon"><i data-lucide="image-off" aria-hidden="true"></i></span>
          <h2>Avoid Common Proof Mistakes</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Do not crop out the date, distance, duration, or source.</li>
            <li>Do not use payment proof as activity proof.</li>
            <li>Explain units or name differences before submitting.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span class="how-card-icon"><i data-lucide="trophy" aria-hidden="true"></i></span>
          <h2>Recognition follows event settings</h2>
          <p>Leaderboards use approved records. Certificates and badges appear only when configured, and are event recognition rather than external accreditation.</p>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span class="how-card-icon"><i data-lucide="shield-check" aria-hidden="true"></i></span>
          <h2>Privacy, safety, and support</h2>
          <p>Proof is limited to authorized reviewers unless explicitly published. Run safely and submit honest records.</p>
          <nav aria-label="Policies and support">
            <a href="/privacy">Privacy</a>
            <a href="/data-usage-policy">Data Usage</a>
            <a href="/faq">FAQ</a>
            <a href="/contact">Contact</a>
          </nav>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section class="how-next" aria-labelledby="next-title">
        <div class="how-next-heading">
          <span class="how-eyebrow">Your next move</span>
          <h2 id="next-title">Continue from your side of the event</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="how-next-grid">
          <article class="how-next-card how-next-runner">
            <span class="how-next-role"><i data-lucide="person-standing" aria-hidden="true"></i>For runners</span>
            <h3>Find your event or return to your entries.</h3>
            <p>Read the event-specific rules before registering or submitting an activity.</p>
            <a class="how-button" href="<%= howItWorksActions.runner.href %>"><i data-lucide="<%= howItWorksActions.runner.icon %>" aria-hidden="true"></i><%= howItWorksActions.runner.label %></a>
          </article>
          <article class="how-next-card how-next-organizer">
            <span class="how-next-role"><i data-lucide="clipboard-check" aria-hidden="true"></i>For organizers</span>
            <h3>Build clear rules and a trusted review flow.</h3>
            <p>Set expectations before registration opens, then review every record consistently.</p>
            <a class="how-button how-button-secondary" href="<%= howItWorksActions.organizer.href %>"><i data-lucide="<%= howItWorksActions.organizer.icon %>" aria-hidden="true"></i><%= howItWorksActions.organizer.label %></a>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>

  <%- include('../layouts/footer') %>
  <script src="/js/main.js"></script>
  <script>if (window.lucide) lucide.createIcons();</script>
</body>
</html>
